
#sample-responsive-images
  h4 Responsive images

  p.align-justify.
    By default, all images are considered responsive and will adjust
    accordingly to the window size. In case you, for any sake, need a
    non responsive image, just add the class <code >.no-responsive</code>
    on it.

  .grid
    .row
      .col.md-6
        h5.align-center Responsive

        p.align-center
          img(src="//placehold.it/800x600", alt="Sample of a responsive image")

        .code-sample
          pre.prettyprint.lang-html.
            &lt;img src="..." alt="..." &gt;


      .col.md-6
        h5.align-center Circle and Thumbnail

        .grid
          .row
            .col.sm-12.md-6
              p.align-center
                img.circle(src="//placehold.it/100x100", alt="Circle image sample")

            .col.sm-12.md-6
              p.align-center
                img.thumb(src="//placehold.it/100x100", alt="Thumbnail image sample")

        .row
          .col.sm-12
            .code-sample
              pre.prettyprint.lang-html.
                &lt;!-- makes a circle image --&gt;
                &lt;img class="circle" ... &gt;

                &lt;!-- makes a square small image --&gt;
                &lt;img class="thumb" ... &gt;
